<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-11-21T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-11-21T07:00:00-05:00" n="574" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d574">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">811.24546/35: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Nouméa</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">MacVitty</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Nouméa</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-11-21T23:00:00+11:00">November
                                    21, 1941—11 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received November 22—5:43 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>28. Reference my telegram 22, October 22, 10 p.m. [<hi rend="italic">a.m.</hi>] In a conversation with the High Commissioner today he
                            said he felt that any improvements in present air bases here should be
                            subject of an agreement between the Free French, Australia and American
                            Governments and that he was averse to any work being done until such an
                            agreement was made. He insisted that the matter should be handled
                            through the Free French representative at Washington, not here.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">MacVitty</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>